        html:"<h2>chunk</h2>\n<h3>Instructions</h3>\n<p>Write a function called <code>Chunk</code> that receives as parameters a slice, <code>slice []int</code>, and a number <code>size int</code>. The goal of this function is to chunk a slice into many sub slices where each sub slice has the length of <code>size</code>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>If the <code>size</code> is <code>0</code> it should print a newline (<code>'\\n'</code>).</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Expected function</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-go\">func Chunk(slice []int, size int) {\n\n}\n</code></pre>\n<h3>Usage</h3>\n<p>Here is a possible program to test your function :</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-go\">package main\n\nfunc main() {\n    Chunk([]int{}, 10)\n    Chunk([]int{0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7}, 0)\n    Chunk([]int{0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7}, 3)\n    Chunk([]int{0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7}, 5)\n    Chunk([]int{0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7}, 4)\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>And its output :</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-console\">$ go run .\n[]\n\n[[0 1 2] [3 4 5] [6 7]]\n[[0 1 2 3 4] [5 6 7]]\n[[0 1 2 3] [4 5 6 7]]\n$\n</code></pre>",
